parameters: So you're the leader of the bandits, Jinrai Nousoka?

Heh! My underling brought me a challenge letter from Mouse
Komachi, but I didn't expect it to be serious. To think that
the famous thief who's been the talk of Edo's common folk
would come to our lair in person. This is quite an honor for
us thieves.

Why did you make this place your bandit lair? The people of
Kondai Village have all been troubled by it, you know?

Kekeke! Well, Edo has strict security, you see. This place,
a bit away from the capital, is comfortable to live in. And
thanks to Mouse Komachi, this old castle in the village is
less likely to catch the shogunate's attention.

What do you say, Miss Mouse Komachi? This must be some kind
of fate. How about joining my band of thieves led by
Nousoka? If we work together, we can earn much more.

I command a group of fifty underlings. If someone as famous
as you joined us, it would add prestige. Let's steal
treasures from all over the country, not just Edo. It's not
a bad deal, right? With the stolen money, we'll all be
rich.

I distribute every single coin from the thousand-ryo boxes I
steal from wealthy merchants to the common people of Edo.
Not a single coin for personal use. I'm different from
bandits like you who steal money and goods from commoners
and villagers!

Keheh, so you're seriously playing the part of a righteous
thief? I thought you were a fellow professional when I
invited you. It's a shame you declined. Then I'll just have
to beat you down and keep you as our pet woman!
Heheh! You let your guard down, Mouse Komachi!

Kekeke! The arrowhead is coated with poison. If you won't
join us, then we'll just have to crush you!
~~~~!! (My body's burning...! Is it poison from the wound!?)

Kekeke! Even with overwhelming support from Edo's commoners,
in front of me, you're just a little girl. A greenhorn.

Haa... haa...! (I need to use antidote herbs to remove the
poison from my body...)

You'll regret coming to the bandit's den alone! You guys,
take down Mouse Komachi and capture her!
--Nousoka Jinrai and his bandit executives are attacking!

You underestimated Mouse Komachi, didn't you? Are you still
going to fight?
Kekeke! Y-yeah, still full of energy...
No use! We can't beat her! Run awayyy!!

W-wait, you guys! Don't leave me...! Don't abandon me, your
leader!
Ah well, your subordinates left you behind. That's too bad.

Ughh! I-I was wrong! I won't steal anymore! Please help me!
I beg of you!

...(Hmm, I'd like to take him to the magistrate's office,
but considering my position, what should I do...)
Eh!? The officials from Edo's magistrate's office!?
Awawa...! To think they'd come from Edo to this village...!?

There's the leader of the bandits in the back! Capture them
all! Don't let anyone escape!

You there from Edo's magistrate's office. Are you the leader
of the bandits, Nousoka Jinrai? You've been causing quite a
ruckus, haven't you?
Wait, please! My nosebleed won't stop...!

No questions asked--I've heard everything from the village
chief. For the crime of leading thieves and threatening the
peace of the village, you cannot be forgiven. Your evil
deeds end here, Nousoka!
Eeeek! It hurts! Don't hit me, please!
Don't move, you bandits! Tie yourselves up quietly!

We've caught all your other companions! Don't think you can
escape!

(This is perfect. It seems the village chief's petition was
successful. I'll leave this to the magistrate's officials
and make my escape!)

Don't think you can escape! We're taking everyone straight
to Edo's prison!

(It seems all the thieves have been captured... Good. Now
the village can return to peace.)

Oh! You're safe? I heard from the village guards that you
went to the bandits' stronghold, so I hurriedly informed the
officials from Edo!

Thank you for calling the officials, village chief. I went
to confront the thieves, but I got scared along the way and
hid in the bushes. Ahaha...

Is that so. Anyway, it's good that you're safe and unharmed.
Thank you for coming to help our village.

No, no... It's good that the thieves were caught and it's
all settled now. Well then, I'll be off--

The day is already tilting towards evening. I need to hurry
back to Edo before it gets dark...

To hide one's identity and do good... I see, the moniker of
a righteous thief is no lie indeed.
--! Who's there!? Identify yourself! I'm not Mouse Komachi!

Heh heh, I haven't mentioned the name Mouse Komachi at all?
Jumping to conclusions is a flaw of yours?
Ugh...! (Damn it...! I revealed my own name!)

Fear not, girl. I am not from the magistrate's office, nor
have I come to capture you.

Don't be so wary. I have no intention of doing anything
right now. I just happened to be scouting in Kamitai Village
and saw your transformed figure... My curiosity was piqued
about what kind of person the phantom thief Mouse Komachi
is, so I was merely observing.

We are seeking strong individuals--warriors who can fight
alongside us with their lives on the line. Whether you could
be useful to our organization or not. Whether you have the
strength and skill to defeat our arch-enemy.

...Organization? What kind of organization? And who are you
planning to fight against when you say arch-enemy?
The opponent is not human. It's a monster--
...! (What murderous intent! My body is trembling...!)

If you stay alive, you will eventually learn about us and
who we fight against.

Farewell, Mouse Komachi. Be careful not to get caught by
the magistrate's office. If you do get caught, consider it a
measure of your power and we shall not meet again.
Wait a minute! At least tell me your name!

~~~~~~! (Gone! She disappeared in an instant!? It's as if
she vanished into thin air...!)

(...No use. It's pointless to ponder the identity of my
opponent. I should hurry back to Edo. I don't want to worry
Oei-san...)
--Karin cautiously made her way back to Edo.

--Stamina and skill power have been \c[24]fully
restored\c[0]!

Mmm, mmm... I can't eat that much food... mmm...
mmm...\I[15]

(...Even if he's a villain, it feels cruel to attack someone
who's sleeping so soundly. I'll let him off this time.)

When I woke up, the bandit gang was annihilated... Maybe I
should quit this life and go back to being an honest man...

When I woke up, the band of thieves had been annihilated...
Maybe it's time for me to quit this life and go back to
being an honest man...

--The man shaved his beard, changed his clothes, and left
the thieves' stronghold behind.
